## §4 raw_91 honest C3 disclosure

**As of 2026-05-12 (cycle 30++++):**
- Axis 1 is REAL-SEMANTICS PROVEN: `sigma 6 = 12` holds genuinely
  against the computable Nat divisor-sum definition.
- Axis 2 is **PROVEN against WEAVE-semantics v3** (hexa-meta `9e44e75`):
  kT is opaque positive ℝ via section variable + `[Fact (0 < kT)]`;
  `landauerFloorPerBit kT = kT · Real.log 2` parametric; `LandauerPass`
  + 3 bonus theorems thread kT through.
- Axis 3 is **PROVEN against WEAVE-semantics v2** (hexa-meta `2c68bea`):
  exponential-in-depth `verifierSteps q := c.size * 2 ^ q.depth + q.payload`
  matching Π^p_2 literature-standard worst case. v3 (recursive verifier
  with WellFoundedRelation termination) is the hardest deferred stretch.
- Axis 4 is **PROVEN against WEAVE-semantics v3** (hexa-meta `9e44e75`):
  `structure ClosureCert (α : Type) [DecidableEq α]` — caveat-bag /
  signer-set / seal snapshots are all `Finset α` (polymorphic).
- All 4 axes sorry-count=0, kernel-checked on lean4 v4.30.0-rc2 +
  Mathlib SHA `f8e537424d154a7eaa025c4abab16c96c626f2e0` via `lake build
  N6` → 1919/1919 jobs PASS.
- **PASS = sorry-free against WEAVE-semantics v2**, NOT against a fully
  polymorphic / algebra-derived / recursive-verifier formulation. v3
  semantics (`[Fact (0 < kT)]` parametrised temperature, recursive
  verifier with `WellFoundedRelation` termination, polymorphic
  `[DecidableEq α]` disclosure carrier) is the cycle-30++++ stretch —
  see §3. Axis 3 v3 + v4 stretches are **NOT v1.x closure blockers NOR
  v2.0.0 cert-strength deliverables**.
- **3 of 4 axes are now at maximum semantics** (1 REAL + 2 v3 + 1 v2);
  the v3 state for Axes 2 + 4 EXCEEDS the v1.x track terminal AND the
  v2.0.0 cert-strength for the formal axes (per `.roadmap.weave` line
